template<typename TimeType , typename StateScalarType >
Eigen::VectorXd tudat::propagators::getZeroProperModeRotationalState ( const simulation_setup::NamedBodyMap &  bodyMap,
const std::shared_ptr< numerical_integrators::IntegratorSettings< TimeType > >  integratorSettings,
const std::shared_ptr< SingleArcPropagatorSettings< StateScalarType > >  propagatorSettings,
const double  bodyMeanRotationRate,
const std::vector< double >  dissipationTimes,
std::vector< std::pair< std::map< TimeType, Eigen::Matrix< StateScalarType, Eigen::Dynamic, 1 > >, std::map< TimeType, Eigen::Matrix< StateScalarType, Eigen::Dynamic, 1 > > > > &  propagatedStates,
std::vector< std::pair< std::map< TimeType, Eigen::Matrix< double, Eigen::Dynamic, 1 > >, std::map< TimeType, Eigen::Matrix< double, Eigen::Dynamic, 1 > > > > &  dependentVariables,
const bool  propagateNominal = true,
const bool  writeToFileInLoop = false,
const std::string  baseFileName = "",
const std::string  outputFolder = input_output::getTudatRootPath( ) 
)

Function to determine the initial rotational state for which the free mode is fully damped, using the approach of Rambaux et al. (2012). Using this method, the dynamics is propagated forward in time with an artificial damping, and backwards in time without this damping. The process is repeated for an ever increasing value of the dissipation time. Using this function, the numerical state and dependent variables at each of the iterations is returned (by reference) by the function. Additionally, the results can be written to files after each iteration.

Parameters
bodyMapMap of bodies in the propagation, with keys the names of the bodies.
integratorSettingsSettings for the numerical integration scheme
propagatorSettingsSettings for the propagator, must include rotational dynamics of only a single body, but may also include translational dynamics.
bodyMeanRotationRateMean rotation rate of body for which the initial state is to be determined, used in the computation of the dissipation matrix.
dissipationTimesList of characteristic times for dissipation matrix (in order of which they will be used)
propagatedStatesNumerical states for each iteration
dependentVariablesDependent variables for each iteration
propagateNominalBoolean designating whether the undamped dynamics is also to be propagated (saved in index 0)
writeToFileInLoopBoolean designating whether the results are written to files after each iteration. NOTE: setting this variable to true will result in propagatedStates and dependentVariables being returned empty (the data being stored in files instead)
baseFileNameFile name prefix used for files, if writeToFileInLoop is true
outputFolderDirectory to which files will be written, if writeToFileInLoop is true

basic_astrodynamics::AccelerationMap &  accelerationModelsPerBody 
)

Function to remove the central gravity acceleration from an AccelerationMap. This is crucial for propagation methods in which the deviation from a reference Kepler orbit is propagated. If the central gravity is a spherical harmonic acceleration, the point mass term is removed by setting the C(0,0) coefficnet to 0

Parameters
bodiesToIntegrateList of names of bodies that are to be integrated numerically.
centralBodiesList of names of bodies of which the central terms are to be removed (per entry of bodiesToIntegrate)
accelerationModelsPerBodyA map containing the list of accelerations acting on each body, identifying the body being acted on and the body acted on by an acceleration. The map has as key a string denoting the name of the body the list of accelerations, provided as the value corresponding to a key, is acting on. This map-value is again a map with string as key, denoting the body exerting the acceleration, and as value a pointer to an acceleration model.
Returns
Functions returning the gravitational parameters of the central terms that were removed.

Function to evaluate the equations of motion for the unifies state model with modified rodrigues parameters (USM6)

Function to evaluate the equations of motion for the unifies state model with modified rodrigues parameters (USM6), providing the time-derivatives of USM6 elements from the accelerations expressed in an RSW frame (see Vallado, 2001). This function takes a number of precomputed quantities as input, to reduce computational burden

Parameters

pParameterVectorValue of the vector gamma (see Vittaldev, 2010)
Returns

Setup CR3BP body map.

Setup CR3BP body map. The two primaries, as well as the third, smaller body to be propagated are defined in the body map. The two primaries are in circular orbit about their barycenter, orbiting it with the same mean motion, so that they stay aligned during propagation.

Parameters

primaryGravitationalParameterGravitational parameter of primary
secondaryGravitationalParameterGravitational parameter of secondary
Returns
Body Map modelling the CR3BP.

Function to propagate the full dynamics problem and the Lambert targeter solution. The function computes the cartesian state as a function of time in two different ways: from the Lambert targeter and from the propagation of the full dynamics problem. The propagator settings for the full problem propagation are directly provided as inputs.

Function to retrieve the list of integrated state types and reference ids. For translational and rotational dynamics, the id refers only to the body being propagated (and the second entry of the pair is empty: ""). For proper time propagation, a body and a reference point may be provided, resulting in non-empty first and second pair entries.

const std::function< Eigen::Matrix< StateScalarType, 6, 1 >(const TimeType) >  integrationToEphemerisFrameFunction = nullptr 
)

Function to convert output of translational motion from the numerical integrator to the required input for the ephemeris. It extracts the state history of a single body from the full list of integrated states Additionally, it changes the origin of the reference frame in which the states are given, by using the integrationToEphemerisFrameFunction input variable.

Parameters
bodyIndexIndex of integrated body for which the state is to be retrieved
startIndexIndex in entries of equationsOfMotionNumericalSolution where the translational states start.
equationsOfMotionNumericalSolutionFull numerical solution of numerical integrator, already converted to Cartesian states (w.r.t. the integration origin of the body of bodyIndex)
ephemerisTableState history of body bodyIndex w.r.t. the origin with which its ephemeris is defined (returned by reference).
integrationToEphemerisFrameFunctionFunction to provide the state of the ephemeris origin of the current body w.r.t. its integration origin.
